post_text:
LAST CHANCE TO REGISTER IS MIDNIGHT TONIGHT!

We're planning to offer our enrolled families a virtual learning option for this school year. If you are interested in the option, you must complete this from by July 28th. If the form is not completed your student(s) will be enrolled for in-person learning.

Students will be given a scheduled time to attend virtual classes led by an RPSA teacher. The curriculum will follow the curriculum in the classroom. By electing this option, you are placed into the virtual classroom for at least one quarter.

It is with a sad and heavy heart that I share news that one of our beloved RPSA Students has passed away.
Ashiya Redmond (7th Grade) passed away after a long battle with cancer.

Tonight (6/29/2020) at 7:00 pm - her family is having a candlelight pink/white balloon memorial for her at her home.
The address is 6920 Parkbelt - Flint, MI

There is also a Go Fund me page to help pay for Ashiya's burial expenses.
https://www.gofundme.com/f/c9bks-ashiya

All are invited to the funeral - Monday 7/6/20
1:00pm is the Family Hour
2:00pm is the funeral

post_text:
Flint Inner City Youth is offering a hockey program and we are kicking off our yearly recruiting drive.

Program starts after Christmas and is open to kids 8-11. First priority is given to Flint city residents.

This is a FREE program and has been nationally recognized by the NHL.

We have recently launched our new website flintinnercityyouthhockey.org , which we are in the process of updating with registration information.

If you know of any kids who might be interested, please pass this info along.
